RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260509T090000
CREATED:20251104T152227Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Here’s a link to the May second Saturday ride: <a href="http
 s://ridewithgps.com/routes/54955439" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.co
 m/<wbr />routes/54955439</a><u></u><u></u></p><p>The RWGPS route uses Pedri
 ck Road to avoid the Stevenson Bridge closure\, but it might be worth a cal
 l to Solano County Department of Resource Management about possible use of 
 Stevenson Bridge on weekends.<u></u><u></u></p><p>The plan is to start from
  Westlake Shopping Center at 8:30 a.m. and bike in a 46 mile counter-clockw
 ise loop to Chepo’s Tamales in Elmira.<u></u><u></u></p><p>More details bel
 ow. Please let me know if you need additional information or have suggestio
 ns for route improvements.<u></u><u></u></p><p>Thanks\,<u></u><u></u></p><p
 >-Anne<u></u><u></u></p><p>(916) 206-2922<u></u><u></u></p><ul><li>Date: Se
 cond Saturday – May 9\, 2026<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start time: <b>8:30</b> 
 a.m.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start location: Westlake Shopping Center\; 1260 
 Lake Boulevard\, Davis.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Distance: 46 miles\, flat.<u>
 </u><u></u></li><li>Contact: Anne Huber\; <a href="mailto:anneh@dcn.org" ta
 rget="_blank">anneh@dcn.org</a>\; 916-206-2922<u></u><u></u></li><li>Servic
 es (Food\, water\, bathrooms): Chepo’s Tamales in Elmira<u></u><u></u></li>
 <li>No need to RSVP<u></u><u></u></li><li>Rain cancellation or postponement
 : communicated via the listserv.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Pace: 14 - 17 mph wi
 th regroups. The speed is meant to be an indicator of speed on flat terrain
  with no wind. People can go faster if they want as long as they are willin
 g to regroup. There might be some stopping for scenery.<u></u><u></u></li><
 li>Route: <a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/54955439" target="_blank"
 >https://ridewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/54955439</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul>
 <p><u></u> <u></u></p><ul><li>For general information about the second Satu
 rday ride and bicycling with the Davis Bike Club\, please see: <a href="htt
 ps://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/" target="_blank">https://davi
 sbikeclub.org/2nd-<wbr />sat-explorer-ride/</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p>T
 his link includes the following: “Cycling has inherent risks. Any cyclist t
 aking part in a DBC ride releases DBC from any liability. Guests are welcom
 e to ride with DBC for one ride\; for subsequent rides\, you must be a memb
 er of the Club. By riding with a DBC group ride you acknowledge that you ha
 ve read and understand this. Helmets are required on all rides.”</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260504T203230Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Second Saturday Explorer Ride
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
